@startuml health-coordinator-architecture
!include _standard-style.puml

title Health Monitoring Architecture (Phase 33 + auto-heal + N/P decoupling)

top to bottom direction

package "Reporters (write signals)" {
  rectangle "ETM (per project)\nenhanced-transcript-monitor.js" as ETM <<core>>
  rectangle "Health verifier CLI\nhealth-verifier.js verify" as VERIFIER <<cli>>
}

package "Coordinator (single SoT)" {
  rectangle "Health coordinator\nhealth-coordinator.js" as COORD <<core>>
  database "/health/state\n(in-memory)" as STATE <<storage>>
  rectangle "HealthRemediationActions\n(host-side dispatcher)" as REMEDIATE <<core>>
  COORD -[#888]- STATE
  COORD -[#888]- REMEDIATE
}

package "Consumers (read state)" {
  rectangle "combined-status-line.js\n(tmux status-right)" as STATUSLINE <<util>>
  rectangle "system-health-dashboard\n:3032 / :3033" as DASHBOARD <<api>>
  rectangle "health-prompt-hook.js" as HOOK <<util>>
}

package "Healable host services" {
  rectangle "ETM, VKB,\nconstraint-monitor,\nllm_cli_proxy,\nobs_api, ..." as TARGETS <<infra>>
}

ETM -[#green,dashed]-> COORD : POST /signals\nlsl_heartbeat\n(every ~2s)
VERIFIER -[#green,dashed]-> COORD : POST /signals\nverify_run\n(one-shot)

STATUSLINE -[#orange]-> COORD : GET /health/state\n(per render)
DASHBOARD  -[#orange]-> COORD : GET /health/state\n(card refresh)
HOOK       -[#orange]-> COORD : GET /health/state\n(per prompt)

DASHBOARD -[#red]-> COORD : POST /health/remediate\n{action, service}\n(Restart-button click)
COORD -[#red]-> REMEDIATE : executeAction(...)
REMEDIATE -[#red]-> TARGETS : spawn / supervisorctl restart\n(host-side)
COORD -[#red,dashed]-> ETM : auto-spawn safety net\n(active transcript +\nno fresh heartbeat,\nrate-limited 30s)

note right of COORD
  Marks LSL entries stopped
  after >15s without a fresh
  heartbeat. Probes services
  (dashboard, vkb, semantic-
  analysis SSE, llm_cli_proxy)
  directly.

  Database sub-checks
  (leveldb_lock_check,
  qdrant_availability,
  graph_integrity) probed
  every tick and mapped to
  passed/failed.

  Network detection (3-signal,
  decoupled from proxy):
  1. Cisco VPN CLI → vpn
  2. utun interface → vpn
  3. BMW DNS + latency:
     <30ms → corporate
     ≥30ms → vpn
     no resolve → open

  Proxy detection (user intent):
  ~/.bash_profile toggle (px alias)
  P:ON  = enabled + CONNECT ok
  P:ERR = enabled + CONNECT fails
  P:OFF = disabled by user

  Stale PID check: probes for
  orphaned consolidation
  heartbeat files.

  ETM safety net (every tick):
  ensureEtmForActiveProjects()
  spawns ETM for any project
  with an active jsonl
  transcript and no live
  heartbeat — 30s rate-limit,
  20s startup grace.
end note

note left of REMEDIATE
  Lazy-imported on first
  /health/remediate call.
  Honors per-action cooldown
  (5 min after failure) and
  hourly rate limit (10/h).
end note

note bottom of DASHBOARD
  AUTO_HEAL_MAP attaches
  auto_heal=true and
  auto_heal_action=<name>
  to violation rows so the
  frontend renders "Enabled"
  and a working Restart
  button.
end note

note bottom of STATUSLINE
  Knowledge pipeline fading:
  📚✅ fresh (<15min)
  📚🟢 recent (15min-1h)
  📚🟠 aging (1-3h)
  📚🟤 stale (3-6h)
  📚⚫ dormant (6-12h)
  📚💤 deep dormant (>12h)
  📚🔴 ONLY when obs_api
       is unreachable (broken)

  N: network = VPN CLI +
     utun + DNS (never proxy)
  P: proxy = ~/.bash_profile
     toggle + CONNECT test
end note

@enduml
